This paper deals with the development of controllers for mobile robots to monitor or sweep a changing environment. The paper focuses on the control aspect of robotics, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of closed paths and speed control to prevent the field from growing unbounded suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the control of a system that is subject to stochasticity, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of linear programming to compute the speed controller suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
